each-description: Output each item in the input array.
key: If all items in the input array pass the predicate subflow, the array is output; otherwise, it is not output.
map-description: Outputs a new array with the results of applying a transform subflow to each element.
filter-description: Outputs a new array with all elements that pass the predicate subflow.
map-transform-description: Convert the input into other content and output it.
predicate-description: When the output is true, it means the item passes; when the output is false, it means the item does not pass.
some-description: If any item in the input array passes the predicate subflow, the array is output; otherwise, it is not output.
switch-by-length: The name of each output handle is an expression. When the length of the input array satisfies the expression, that interface outputs the original array; otherwise, it does not output anything.
package-description: Util Nodes for handling Array data.
all-passed: Whether all items passed the predicate subflow.
filltered-array: A new Array with items passed the predicate subflow.
mapped-array: A new array of items mapped by the transform subflow.
any-passed: Whether any item passed the predicate subflow.
